  "summary": "Following Muto's hypothesis regarding the Mikumo incident, a group including Kogen, the police chief, Horikoshi, and others decides to open a coffin in the underground mortuary of Kurokawa City. Kogen agrees to the request, partly because he is a primary suspect and seeks self-preservation. Amid heavy snowfall, the group descends a wide staircase into a dark, pungent underground room containing several coffins, including those of Takao and Kimiko.\n\nThey focus on the stone coffin of Tadao, which features a crystal lid engraved with \"TAJIMA·I.\" As the grave diggers and Detective Horikoshi lift the lid, the group expects to find Takeda. Instead, they discover the corpse of Mutsuji, who had died a month prior. The discovery causes chaos and psychological distress among the witnesses, including Mochizuki and Woodmore. Mutsuji’s body has been cut into two halves, mirroring the state of previous victims, suggesting the work of a serial killer.\n\nIn a separate narrative segment, a man named McArthur, dressed in a tailcoat and top hat, arrives at a desolate house. He initially mistakes the narrator for Kumigami and then for Shimomura. Upon learning that Jinmao Jingma passed away the previous day, McArthur’s demeanor shifts, and his gaze becomes sharp as he asks if Jingma was killed.",
